text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia caesariata is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt  region of Western Australia.The dense rounded shrub typically grows to a height of 0.6 to 1.6 metres (2.0 to 5.2 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
